parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leak Due to Faulty Quick Disconnect Fitting
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel leak can cause a fire, potentially leading to serious injury or death. Even if a fire does not occur, the fuel leak can still cause damage to the vehicle and surrounding property.
symptoms: fuel leaking from the fuel line
fuel pouring onto the exhaust piping
fuel collecting on the cylinder head.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A corroded fuel cutoff valve can cause a fuel leak, leading to a fire hazard and potentially serious injury or death.
symptoms: Fuel leaking from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective fuel tank can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, or environmental hazards.
symptoms: weeping or seeping of fuel from the tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the fuel lines can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, or environmental hazards.
symptoms: fuel dripping from the fuel lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the quick disconnect can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, accidents, or environmental hazards.
symptoms: fuel dripping from the quick disconnect.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS unit can lead to a loss of vehicle stability and control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially during hard braking or slippery road conditions.
symptoms: The ABS warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the ABS system does not function properly
the vehicle's brakes may lock up or vibrate
the vehicle may pull to one side while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Spline Input Shaft Wear and Clutch Plate Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The wear on the spline input shaft and failure of the clutch plate can cause grinding noises, difficulty shifting gears, and loss of acceleration, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
